@host = http://localhost:3000
@baseUrl = {{host}}/api/v1
@token = Bearer YOUR_JWT_TOKEN_HERE

### ============================================
### RBAC MODULE - Role-Based Access Control
### ============================================

### ROLES - List Roles
GET {{baseUrl}}/rbac/roles?page=1&limit=20
Authorization: {{token}}

### ROLES - Get Role
GET {{baseUrl}}/rbac/roles/:roleId
Authorization: {{token}}

### ROLES - Create Role
POST {{baseUrl}}/rbac/roles
Authorization: {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Manager",
  "description": "Manager role with limited admin access",
  "permissions": ["read:contacts", "write:contacts", "read:deals"]
}

### ROLES - Update Role
PUT {{baseUrl}}/rbac/roles/:roleId
Authorization: {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "permissions": ["read:contacts", "write:contacts", "read:deals", "write:deals"]
}

### PERMISSIONS - List Permissions
GET {{baseUrl}}/rbac/permissions
Authorization: {{token}}

### USERS - Assign Role
POST {{baseUrl}}/rbac/users/:userId/roles
Authorization: {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "roleId": "role-uuid"
}

### USERS - Remove Role
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/rbac/users/:userId/roles/:roleId
Authorization: {{token}}

### Notes:
### - All endpoints require authentication
### - Standard roles: admin, manager, user, guest
### - Replace UUIDs with actual IDs from your database
